README:
PJFry 1.0.0 - one loop tensor integral library
(see LICENSE for the status of this software)

The algorithms are based on the results of http://arxiv.org/abs/1009.4436
Please cite arXiv:1009.4436v3 [hep-ph] if you use PJFry in scientific publications.

For more information and the latest source code,
please visit project page at https://github.com/Vayu/PJFry/

Branches:
 'master'  - the latest stable version
 'develop' - the latest development state, contains newest fetures, possibly untested

To build on Unix/Linux and similar systems:
   ./configure ; make ; make install
see INSTALL file for the detailed explanation of ./configure options

The project subdirectories are:
./src       - library source code
./mlink     - MathLink interface
./examples  - FORTRAN examples of library use (build with 'make check')

To report bugs, please create an issue at:
  https://github.com/Vayu/PJFry/issues

Valery Yundin
description: PJFry - library for one-loop tensor integrals
